[SN]TITLE[SN]
Filipe Morais: Bolton Wanderers sign winger after Bradford City exit

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bolton Wanderers have signed winger Filipe Morais on a deal until the end of the season following his release by fellow League One club Bradford City.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 31-year-old former Chelsea trainee left the Bantams by mutual consent on transfer deadline day.
The former Portugal Under-21 international has played for 10 clubs during his career including Hibernian, Oldham and Stevenage.
He is available for Saturday's trip to MK Dons, for whom he played in 2006.
